HEADWORD: Persiflage
<hw>Per`si`flage"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>persifler</ets> to quiz, fr. L. <ets>per</ets> + <ets>siffler</ets>
to whistle, hiss, L. <ets>sibilare</ets>, <ets>sifilare</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Frivolous or bantering talk; a frivolous manner of treating any
subject, whether serious or otherwise; light raillery.</def>
<rj><au>Hannah More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persifleur</ent>⟦br⟧
